om.administration.questionbank
Class QuestionBankCleaner

java.lang.Object
  om.administration.questionbank.QuestionBankCleaner
All Implemented Interfaces:
CleanQuestionBanks
public class QuestionBankCleaner
extends java.lang.Object
implements CleanQuestionBanks

This implementation of the CleanQuestionBanks is particuarly memory hungry and there are a few places with higher performance questions. This is due to what has to happen and a reluctance on heavy IO otherwise.

Note that this is implemented with a single thread approach.

Author:
Trevor Hinson

isOpenForAnyStudent

protected boolean isOpenForAnyStudent(java.lang.String query,
                                      DatabaseAccess da)
                               throws CleaningException
Checks the underlying persistence mechanism to ensure that there is not a version of the given question still open within the database. IF there is a version open then the method returns true and the question itself is therefore still required for that student and therefore can not be classified as superfluous as a result. Defaults to true in order to be safe as those that are set to open will not appear within the superfluous listing.

Parameters:
fullName -
da -
Returns:
Throws:
CleaningException
